Installation
============

## Create a configuration for your environment

### create a file environment.py in <project root>

make sure to replace name by your *env name*

	# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
	NAME = 'staging'
	IS_FOR_DEVELOPMENT = True

### Create a file configuration/_50_env_<your env name>.py
use e..g configuration/_50_env_boerni.py as 

## Setup virtualenv

 * chdir to <project root>
 * mkdir env_default
 * virtualenv --no-site-packages env_default
 * source env_default/bin/activate
 * pip install -r REQUIREMENTS
